Pull the code from git hub
Run mvn clean install
Run mvn assembly:assembly
Go to the target folder and unzip the twitterCli.zip.
Go into the unzipped folder and run the below command
java -jar twitterCli-1.0.jar HOST_NAME HOST_PORT FILTER  TIME_IN_SECONDS

    where HOST_NAME is the host where streaming server is running
          PORT is the one which streaming server is listening for requests
          FILTER is the keyword you want to look for
          TIME_IN_SECONDS is the pause between each request polling. Default value is 5 seconds.


    FILTER is a single word and multiple keywords are not supported

    Except TIME_IN_SECONDS, all arguments are mandatory.


Streaming Server can be downloaded from

    https://github.com/Ramkumar83/twitterStreamServer